Colin and all,

Okay...here&#39;s my suggested format for network XML. 
(I&#39;m using Colin&#39;s recent recurrent XOR network as an
example):

&lt;network&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;Colin&#39;s XOR Network&lt;/title&gt; 
  &lt;neuron id=&quot;0&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
hint-position=&quot;1&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;neuron id=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
hint-position=&quot;2&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;neuron id=&quot;2&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
hint-position=&quot;3&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;neuron id=&quot;3&quot; type=&quot;out&quot; hint-layer=&quot;2&quot;
hint-position=&quot;1&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;connection id=&quot;4&quot; src-id=&quot;0&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;1.64327624043105&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;connection id=&quot;5&quot; src-id=&quot;1&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;-3.3017311279049&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;connection id=&quot;6&quot; src-id=&quot;2&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;-3.3025163810043&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;connection id=&quot;7&quot; src-id=&quot;3&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
recurrent=&quot;true&quot; weight=&quot;-7.44947553716588&quot; /&gt; 
  &lt;/network&gt;

Neurons need to have a layer designation, denoted by
the &quot;hint-layer&quot; attribute, and a position within that
layer, denoted by the &quot;hint-position&quot; attribute.  This
way, you can use whatever logic you like to place
neurons in any given layer and position, and the XSL
style sheet can just handle laying them out and
graphing them.

Note that connections need to have an id, as well as a
&quot;recurrent&quot; attribute.

I&#39;ll write a second XSL style sheet to handle the
transformation from this XML into a form that my
current style sheet can parse into an SVG image. 
Again, all you&#39;ll need to do is make sure your XML is
in the above format, that all the files are in the
same directory, that you have Xalan and an SVG plug-in
installed, and then type &quot;draw [xml-filename]&quot;.

Just wondering...Colin and Ken have expressed an
interest in using these tools.  Anyone else?

Derek

